      %h3{ id: 'users' } USER
      %h4{ id: 'benefits-of-becoming-an-ace-user' } Benefits of becoming an ACE User

      %p Anyone can navigate to the ACE site to search for data and to download data, including people without ACE user accounts. You can use the Arctic Collaborative Environment without registering but there are some benefits to getting your own ACE user account.

      %p With an ACE user account you can publish datasets and you can personalize your experience. Registered ACE users can “follow” datasets. To register create a ACE user ID using the instructions below.


      %h4{id: 'create-a-user-account' } Create a User Account

      %p To create a user account, use the “Register” link at the top of any page. You will be asked for the following:

      %dl.dl-horizontal
        %dt Username
        %dd Choose a username containing only letters, numbers, and dashes (- and _ characters). For example, “asmith” or “a_smith56”
        %dt Full name
        %dd Your name to be displayed on your user profile
        %dt E-mail address
        %dd This will not be visible to other users
        %dt Password
        %dd Enter your password, re-enter it to confirm

        %h4{ id: 'manage-your-account' } Manage your Account

        %p Click on your own name to see your user profile. Select "Manage" button to make changes to your profile. Here you can change your Full Name and email, add a short biography and also change your password.

        %h4{ id: 'logging-in' } Logging In

        %pClick the "Log in" button in the top upper right corner of the ACE site. You'll be prompted to log in with your username and password. If you have forgotten your password, click "Forgot your password?". By entering your username you can request to reset your password.

        %h4{ id: 'api-key' } API key
        %p Your API key is private.

        %a{ href: "#user" } Back to Top

        %h3{ id: 'data-providers' } Data Providers

        %p Data providers are the primary way to control who can see, create and update datasets in CKAN. Each dataset can belong to a single data provider, and each data provider controls access to its datasets. Each data provider has its own landing page where users can view information about the data provider and search the data provider-owned datasets.

